name: Remove elements that have the same product of digits
description:
You are given an array {a, b, c, ... , n}

You are required to find all the elements that have the same product of digits.

You should return an array that has all of these elements removed.

The elements in the array will always be >= 10

Example:


clear( {19, 32, 61, 33, 77} ) should return {77}

since "1x9 = 3x3 = 9" and "3x2 = 6x1 = 6"
